<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="25" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="8.[148,788,269,677]" pageId="8" pageNumber="25">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[148,281,269,293]" pageId="8" pageNumber="25">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[148,249,269,293]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="25">Remarks</emphasis>
. –
</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Zhang &amp; Yang &amp; Grootaert, 2008" authorityName="Zhang &amp; Yang &amp; Grootaert" authorityYear="2008" box="[293,536,270,293]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Hercostomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="25" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="limosus" status="new species">
<emphasis box="[293,536,270,293]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="25">Hercostomus limosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[554,695,270,293]" pageId="8" pageNumber="25" rank="species">new species</taxonomicNameLabel>
, and 
<taxonomicName authority="Zhang &amp; Yang &amp; Grootaert, 2008" authorityName="Zhang &amp; Yang &amp; Grootaert" authorityYear="2008" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Hercostomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="25" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lanceolatus" status="new species">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="25">H. lanceolatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[293,431,302,325]" pageId="8" pageNumber="25" rank="species">new species</taxonomicNameLabel>
, are both similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Becker, 1922" authorityName="Becker" authorityYear="1922" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Hercostomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="25" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="notatus">
<emphasis box="[669,787,302,325]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="25">H. notatus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Becker, T" box="[148,309,334,357]" pageId="8" pageNumber="25" pagination="1 - 247" refId="ref7585" refString="Becker, T. H., 1922. Dipterologische Studien Dolichopodidae der Indo-Australischen Region. Capita Zoologica, 1: 1 - 247." type="journal article" year="1922">Becker, 1922</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, from 
<collectingCountry box="[391,476,334,357]" name="Taiwan" pageId="8" pageNumber="25">Taiwan</collectingCountry>
in having a wing stigma. Examination of a male (Formosa Sauter, Takao 
<date box="[681,783,366,389]" pageId="8" pageNumber="25" value="1907-05-03">1907.V.3</date>
; 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Becker" authorityYear="1922" box="[148,257,398,421]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Hercostomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="25" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="notatus">
<emphasis box="[148,257,398,421]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="25">H. notatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
det. Becker), here designated as 
<typeStatus box="[596,693,398,421]" pageId="8" pageNumber="25">lectotype</typeStatus>
revealed that it has R 
<subScript attach="left" box="[291,315,442,456]" fontSize="6" pageId="8" pageNumber="25">4+5</subScript>
thickened from its base onwards and the thickening ends halfway the vein i.e. shortly beyond the stigma. 
